    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.3"/>
                
                <note>ans. 6/5/72</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">3</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <unclear reason="missing"/>
                    Bloomington, Ill. 
                    61701
                
                    <note>(posted in May 1972</note>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>John Gneisenau Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Skyrim, Rd. 7</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Sir:</salute> 
                </opener>
                <p>When I was in the fifth grade in Hawthorne School you came to talk about one of your books of poetry and gave us a signed copy. I got to shake hands with you.</p>
                
                <p>I am now in the seventh grade at Bloomington Junior High School in Bloomington Illinois. I decided to write to you because I remember the rush to check-out your book. I was first. I would like you to send me your autograph if at all possible. Please write back.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours truly,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Greg George</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <opener><hi rend="caps">P.S.</hi></opener> <p>I enclose a Self Addressed Stamped Envelope</p>
                </postscript>
                
                <fw>2</fw>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
